urlText: Opal can be used between Wollongong and Moss Vale, Exeter and Bundanoon stations.
content:
If travelling by Coach between Wollongong station and Moss Vale, Exeter or Bundanoon stations you can use your Opal card or contactless card or device to tap on or off at your origin/destination station provided the origin/destination is an Opal enabled station.

If travelling onto Goulburn, or other Opal enabled station along the Southern Highlands Line, you should not tap off when transferring from Coach to an Intercity train but instead tap off at your destination station.

Booking is not required for Opal customers on this route.
subtitle: Opal can be used between Wollongong and Moss Vale, Exeter and Bundanoon stations.

urlText: Opal can be used between Bathurst and Lithgow Stations when booked
content: If travelling by Coach to or from Bathurst you can use your Opal card or contactless card or device to tap on or off at Bathurst station and your origin/destination station provided the origin/destination is an Opal enabled station. When using Opal you will need to reserve a seat, at no cost, through the Contact Centre by calling 13 22 32 (Between 07:00 to 22:00 each day).
subtitle: Opal can be used between Bathurst and Lithgow Stations when booked

urlText: The Star temporary stop closure
content:
From 6am Wednesday 21 July until Monday 11 October, L1 Dulwich Hill Line light rail services will not stop at The Star while the whole casino complex is closed under NSW Government COVID-19 guidelines.

No other stops are affected.

Please use the alternative nearest stops: Pyrmont Bay or John Street Square (approx. 5 minute walk).

All Sydney Light Rail services continue to run at current reduced frequencies. L1 line night services from 11pm to 6am continue to be suspended between Central and The Star.

Please allow extra travel time and use the Trip Planner or check travel alerts to see if your travel is affected.
subtitle: The Star temporary stop closure

urlText: Route will be withdrawn from Sunday 18 October
content:
From Sunday 18 October this route will be withdrawn with existing trips converted to route 607X services between the City and Bella Vista.

If you are travelling from the City beyond Bella Vista, you can still use the Nightride N92.

Please see the North West and North Shore Sydney bus service changes news article for more details.

urlText: Route and timetable changes from Sunday 18 October
content:
From Sunday 18 October this route will have route and timetable changes.

The route will be truncated between Kellyville and Castle Hill on weekdays. All services will still operate between Castle Hill and the City.

Alternative travel options between Kellyville and Castle Hill are available on routes 601, 626, 632, 633 and 715, providing connects to Sydney Metro or other bus services at Hills Showground or Castle Hill Stations.

Please see the North West and North Shore Sydney bus service changes news article for more details.
subtitle: Route and timetable changes from Sunday 18 October

urlText: Strathfield Station bus stand changes
content:
From 2am Saturday 9 to 2am Monday 11 October, route 450 bus services will not stop at Strathfield Station, Albert Rd, Stand F (213563) due to trackwork.

Please use Strathfield Station, Albert Rd, Stand L (213519).
subtitle: Strathfield Station bus stand changes
